cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper deals with text style transfer, which is a natural language processing task, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses pre-trained continuous distributed style representations, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves training a model to transfer text sentiment, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories.
